<p>
  <span class="nym">Rufus</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>rufus</i> 'red, ruddy'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a minor New Testament character and a number of early saints and martyrs. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Rufe</i>, <i>Rufus</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p><i>Rufus</i> was also one of the most common of the ancient Roman <i>cognomina</i>.</p>
</div>
  


